# Local saves only — never to SharePoint

Treat any path under a synced SharePoint / OneDrive **client** workspace as **read-only**. Read inputs from there; never write outputs back.

## What counts as "SharePoint"

Any path containing a client SharePoint document library, e.g.:

- `…\OneDrive - McKinsey & Company\<engagement> - <client> - <site> - Documents\…`
- `…\OneDrive - McKinsey & Company\2026 CMCSA - Cable - Documents\…`

The local workspace root (`…\Documents\cursor_comcast\slide_generation_base\…`) is **not** SharePoint even though it sits under OneDrive — it's the local repo and is the correct write target.

## Where to save outputs

Always write to the local workspace:

- Session deliverables → `work/sessions/<YYYY-MM-DD-topic-slug>/`
- Raw source files brought in for ingest → `knowledge/content/raw/`
- Wiki pages → `knowledge/content/wiki/`
- Final slide outputs → `work/sessions/<YYYY-MM-DD-topic-slug>/slide-deck.pptx`

If the user wants the file mirrored to a SharePoint folder, ask first and confirm the path — do not assume.

## Examples

❌ BAD — writing a mapped workbook directly into the client SharePoint folder without asking:

```python
out = r"C:\Users\Alan Ma\OneDrive - McKinsey & Company\2026 CMCSA - Cable - Documents\…\mapping.xlsx"
wb.save(out)
```

✅ GOOD — write to the local session folder, then ask before mirroring:

```python
out = SESSION / "mapping.xlsx"
wb.save(out)
# Mirror to SharePoint only if explicitly requested by the user.
```
